cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.NE, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with deep learning and optimization techniques for training large neural networks on large datasets, specifically on the ImageNet dataset. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper focuses on visual recognition models. The paper also discusses distributed computing and parallel processing, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes new techniques for adjusting learning rates and overcoming optimization challenges, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
